sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration.doc:
A class to describe message configuration.

A message configuration object provide all characteristics needed to validate a xml message.

sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration.code.doc: Code is a mnemonic value for a specific message

sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration.autode.doc: Return the sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration object associated to the data parameter by matching with the xmlns attribute

sepa_sctinst.Message.doc: All sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration objects available on the SCTInst schema (Interbank and C2B)

sepa_sctinst.schema_validation.SchemaVal.doc:
A class to validate SCTInst messages.

A schema validation object provide a schema validation method

XSD Validation for SCTInst messages where data is a XML message as string, payment_conf is an sepa_sctinst.MessageConfiguration wich provide the schema to use for validation Returns a dict with isValid key and error_messages key if isValid = False

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader.doc:
A class to represent the group header in interbank SCTInst message

Set of characteristics shared by all individual transactions included in the message.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader.messag.doc: Message Identification assigned by the instructing party, and sent to the next party in the chain to unambiguously identify the message.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader.creati.doc: Date and time at which the message was created.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader.interb.doc: Date on which the amount of money ceases to be available to the agent that owes it and when the amount of money becomes available to the agent to which it is due.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader.sttlmt.doc: Method used to settle the (batch of) payment instructions.Only CLRG, INGA and INDA are allowed

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Participant.doc: A class to represent the group header in interbank SCTInst message

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Participant.bic.doc: The BIC code of the participant Bank

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.doc: A class to represent the group header in interbank SCTInst message

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.amount.doc: The amount of the SCT Inst in Euro

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.end_to.doc: Original End To End Identification. Unique identification, as assigned by the original initiating party

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.tx_id.doc: Original Transaction Identification. Unique identification, as assigned by the original first instructing agent

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.accept.doc: Point in time when the payment order from the initiating party meets the processing conditions of the account servicing agent.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction.refere.doc: Reference information provided by the creditor to allow the identification of the underlying documents.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst.doc: A class to represent a SCTInst interbank message

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst.group_head.doc: sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.GroupHeader object shared by all individual transactions included in the message.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst.transactio.doc: sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.Transaction object give information about the transaction.

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst.random.doc:
Generate random SCTInst object

Returns sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst object with random value

sepa_sctinst.sct_inst.SCTInst.to_xml.doc: Generate message as XML Document Returns a string as XML dcoument

Transaction

SCTInstC2B constructor

Generate random SCTInstC2B object

Returns: SCTInstC2B: SCTInstC2B object with random value
